bilingual.target: 在巴西，人们有时会亲吻。

bilingual.source: American people shake hands and sometimes kiss.
In Russia, people usually kiss three times, left, right, left.
bilingual.target: 在俄罗斯，人们通常亲吻三次，左，右，左。

bilingual.source: Lingling, you know, in Russia, people usually kiss three times.
bilingual.target: 玲玲，你知道，在俄罗斯，人们通常亲吻三次。

bilingual.source: In the US some people shake hands, and some kiss or hug each other.
bilingual.target: 在美国，有些人握手，有些人亲吻或拥抱。

bilingual.source: Later I found out French people are supposed to kiss when they see each other.
bilingual.target: 后来我发现法国人见面时应该亲吻。

bilingual.source: She sealed the envelope with a kiss.
bilingual.target: 她用一个吻封住了信封。
他总是忘不了她的晚安吻。

list.abstract: Kiss，英文单词，作动词、名词，翻译为亲吻、（一球与另一球）轻擦、小甜酥饼等意思，最初源自古英语的cyssan。
亲吻是指用嘴唇触碰其他事物，通常是另一个人。吻有各种各样的类型：有情人之间的热烈的亲吻，有父母对孩子爱惜的吻，有朋友之间表示友好、尊敬的吻，就连两国首脑见面时，也常常拥抱亲吻表示敬意。亲吻不一定是接吻，也不一定是情侣之间才有的行为。

yingyinNormal.en: So, where's Hans? What happened to your kiss?
yingyinNormal.zh: 汉斯在哪？你的吻怎么样了？

yingyinNormal.en: An act of true love? A true love's kiss, perhaps?
yingyinNormal.zh: 真爱的行动？真爱之吻，也许？

yingyinNormal.en: And this was just a kiss. A kiss is nothing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们俩只是接吻而已，没什么大不了的。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll kiss your staff. Too late.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我亲吻权杖。太晚了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb》

yingyinNormal.en: A kiss with Aidan. It was a kiss. We have a history. It was just a kiss. Say nothing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 和艾登接吻。吻吻而已。我们曾经相爱过。只是一个吻，什么也别说了。

yingyinNormal.en: What kind of a kiss? A big kiss. On the mouth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是，是哪种吻啊？长吻啊，嘴对嘴的。

yingyinNormal.en: We had our first kiss. On this very couch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们第一次接吻。就在这张沙发上。

yingyinNormal.en: First kiss I ever had was on that rampart.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的初吻就是在那座城墙上献出的。

yingyinNormal.en: You are speaking with a pharaoh. Kiss my staff.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在跟法老说话。亲吻我的权杖。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb》

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, Max, I think we're witnessing his first kiss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 麦克斯，我们在见证他的初吻。

yingyinNormal.en: I will never kiss another man other than my husband.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除了我的丈夫，我绝不亲吻任何男人。

yingyinNormal.en: This might explain why people never forget their first kiss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这也许能解释为何人们总忘不了初吻。

yingyinNormal.en: A true love's kiss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个真爱之吻。

yingyinNormal.en: I'd kiss you again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会再吻你一次。

yingyinNormal.en: Honey, I swear it we just kissed. It was just a kiss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们只是吻了一下。只是一个吻。

yingyinNormal.en: Penny kissing me is not insane. She used to kiss me all the time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩妮吻我可不是什么疯狂之举，她以前经常吻我的。

yingyinNormal.en: Aren't you gonna give me a kiss? Okay, I will. But right after you tell me who the hell you are.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不吻我吗？好吧，但我吻了你之后，你得告诉我你是谁。

yingyinNormal.en: You come all the way home, and I don't get a kiss?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好不容易回趟家，都不吻我一下吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Kiss me first. And I promise I won't keep you waiting too long.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先吻我，我保证，我不会让你等太久。

yingyinNormal.en: I sat in the second carriage because I thought you might kiss me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我坐在第二节车厢里因为我想你可能会吻我。

examination_example.sentence: However, gender matters more for them because cheek-<highlight>kissing</highlight> often only happens between women or a man and a woman but not two men.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，性别对他们来说更重要，因为亲吻脸颊通常只发生在女性之间或男性与女性之间，而不是两个男性之间。

examination_example.sentence: While cheek-<highlight>kissing</highlight> for Latin Americans is also a universal greeting form, it does not require such a high degree of relational closeness.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然对拉丁美洲人来说，亲脸颊也是一种普遍的问候形式，但它并不需要如此程度的关系亲密。

examination_example.sentence: If that weren't implied by the landscape—rolling green hills, sun-<highlight>kissed</highlight> flowers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 连绵起伏的青山、棕榈树、沐浴着阳光的鲜花，如果这些还没有暗示出这一点的话。

examination_example.sentence: Jo looked at Amy in her bed and gave her a big <highlight>kiss</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 乔看着躺在床上的艾米，给了她一个大大的吻。

examination_example.sentence: But when the virus is going around, too many <highlight>kisses</highlight> are not good.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是当病毒四处传播时，过多的亲吻是不好的。

examination_example.sentence: I couldn’t find words to describe their joy when they received an ice-cream, a ball or even a <highlight>kiss</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我找不到语言来描述他们收到冰激凌，一个球甚至一个吻的时候的喜悦。

examination_example.sentence: She bent down to <highlight>kiss</highlight> the frog.
According to her, if you want to say hello to others, do not hug or <highlight>kiss</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 据她说，如果你想和别人打招呼，不要拥抱或亲吻。

examination_example.sentence: When they meet, they always hug or <highlight>kiss</highlight> each other.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当他们见面时，他们总是互相拥抱或亲吻。
